abstract: If the Big Ten chooses to add members, it is possible that it would set off a series of dramatic changes in other conferences.
snippet: If the Big Ten chooses to add members, it is possible that it would set off a series of dramatic changes in other conferences.
lead_paragraph: When the Big Ten Conference announced last month that it was considering expansion, the college sports world began a high-stakes game of musical chairs that will be influenced by athletic performance, academic standing, geography and money. Several universities have begun to circle hopefully, lobbying, eyeing a potential seat in new conference alignments, wanting desperately to avoid being left out of the big-money alliances once the music stops.

abstract: More letters in response to Katie Roiphe’s essay about sex and the American male novelist.
snippet: More letters in response to Katie Roiphe’s essay about sex and the American male novelist.
lead_paragraph: On Jan. 3, the Book Review published Katie Roiphe’s cover essay on the aggressively virile sexual attitudes of the Great Male Novelists of the postwar period (Roth, Updike, Mailer, Bellow) contrasted with the mores of their more thoughtful, cuddly contemporary counterparts (Franzen, Chabon, Eggers, Wallace).
